&lt;h2 id="what-is-it">What is it?&lt;a class="td-heading-self-link" href="#what-is-it" aria-label="Heading self-link">&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Parallel ROMs (OTP-ROMs, EPROMs, EEPROMs, NOR flash, etc.) can be used as simple, programmable logic devices.&lt;br>
They can be programmed to hold a lookup-table / bit stream, which will emulate logic functions (like 74-series logic) by responding to a certain pattern on the &amp;ldquo;input&amp;rdquo; (aka address lines) with a pre-calculated &amp;ldquo;output&amp;rdquo; (on the data lines).&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>ISA-over-USB</title><link>https://kittenlabs.de/isa-over-usb/</link><pubDate>Wed, 14 Oct 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://kittenlabs.de/isa-over-usb/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-is-it">What is it?&lt;a class="td-heading-self-link" href="#what-is-it" aria-label="Heading self-link">&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>This project allows the use of ISA extension cards on a modern computer over a USB interface.&lt;br>
The main project goal was to learn about the ISA bus, not to build a polished product.&lt;/p>


&lt;div class="alert alert-primary" role="alert">
&lt;h4 class="alert-heading">USB limitations&lt;/h4>

 &lt;p>USB has inherent limits to the minimum latency, defined by the frame timing in the USB specification.&lt;br>
This means that a USB 1.1 attached device will only ever be able to handle &lt;strong>1000 transfers per second&lt;/strong>.&lt;br>
USB 2.0 increases this limit to 8000 transfers per second (125μs frame time), which is still way to slow for most applications.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>FlexibleLOM PCIe adapter</title><link>https://kittenlabs.de/flexiblelom/</link><pubDate>Sun, 27 Sep 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://kittenlabs.de/flexiblelom/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;img src="featured-adapter.jpeg" width="49%" alt="FlexibleLOM adapter"> &lt;img src="installed.jpeg" width="49%" alt="FlexibleLOM adapter installed in PC">&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="what-is-it">What is it?&lt;a class="td-heading-self-link" href="#what-is-it" aria-label="Heading self-link">&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>This passive adapter PCB allows the use of HP FlexibleLOM extension cards (like 10/40 GbE network cards) in regular PCIe slots.
FlexibleLOM extension cards are available used at very low prices (due to them not being PCIe compatible, despite using the same physical slot).&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="development-photos">Development photos&lt;a class="td-heading-self-link" href="#development-photos" aria-label="Heading self-link">&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>
